Business Brief -- West Co.:
   Loss Widened in 4th Period
   After Restructuring Charge
William G. Little, president and chief executive officer,
said the restructuring will position the company for success
in 1992. "By centering our manufacturing on key sites and
creating a strategic marketing alliance with our Japanese and
European partners, we have enhanced {our} strengths," he
said.
   For the full year, the company reported a net loss of
$14.7 million, or 95 cents a share, compared with net income
of $4.3 million, or 27 cents a share. Sales rose 2% to $329.6
million. The latest year-end results include a $6.3 million
charge related to the adoption of a new accounting rule for
retiree benefit costs.